  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. The governing Requirement mandates a controlled-experiment verification method for hemolysis validation. The supporting validation activity was conducted as an observational study drawing on clinical registry data and published pump-performance surveillance records — a method that the narrative characterises as functionally equivalent to a controlled experiment because operating conditions were tightly bounded and confounders were statistically adjusted. However, the structured activityType field records 'observational-study', which does not satisfy the 'controlled-experiment' requirement, breaking the inference link (W-AR-03). Decision outcome recorded as Accepted.",
