    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vad-hemolysis-observational-2024",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "VAD hemolysis validation — observational registry study",
      "description": "Hemolysis index predictions from the CFD model were compared against plasma free haemoglobin measurements drawn from a multi-centre VAD implant registry (n = 312 patient-pump pairs, 5 flow-speed operating points each). Statistical adjustment for haematocrit, anticoagulation regimen and implant duration was applied using propensity-score matching, yielding an adjusted mean absolute error of 0.0031 g/dL across all operating points. The study team concluded that the tightly bounded operating envelope and propensity-score adjustment rendered the observational dataset functionally equivalent to a controlled experiment, providing high confidence in the CFD hemolysis predictions. Uncertainty bands derived from Monte Carlo sampling overlapped the registry interquartile range at all five operating points, further supporting model adequacy.",
